ProtoDefines:
. "We say that $f(x)$ \term{ approaches the limit $L$ as $x$ 
   approaches } $\infty$, and write $$ \lim_{x\to\infty} 
   f(x)=L, $$ if $f$ is defined on an interval $(a,\infty)$ 
   and, for each $\epsilon>0$, there is a number $\beta$ such 
   that $$ |f(x)-L|<\epsilon\quad \quad if \quad x>\beta. $$"
